p: No statistically significant differences were found in lipolysis rate (nmol/10 6 cells) or isoproterenol-induced lipolysis rate ( Figures 5C,D) amongst the three groups. However, oleate incorporation into lipids was 130% higher ( p = 0.01) in HFD (39573.1 nmol/10 6 cells) than NFD (17189.9 nmol/10 6 cells). Additionally, GbE supplementation showed a strong tendency to reduce this parameter by 43% ( p = 0.06) (22412.7 nmol/10 6 cells) in relation to HFD ( Figure 5E). Acetate incorporation into lipids (nmol/10 6 cells) was reduced by 115% ( p = 0.003) in HFD+GbE (19286.5 nmol/10 6 cells) in relation to HFD (41560.2 nmol/10 6 cells) ( Figure 5F).
